default&#xa0;default1.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe Local Government 
defaultAssociation (LGA) is the national voice of local government.
default 
defaultWe work with councils to support, promote and improve local government.
default&#xa0;
default1.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWe are a politically-led, cross party organisation which
default 
defaultworks on behalf of councils to ensure local government has a 
defaultstrong, credible voice with national government.
default 
defaultWe aim to influence and set the political agenda on the issues that matter to councils so they are able to deliver local solutions to national problems.
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;default2.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultT
defaulthe LGA is advocating a radical new approach
default which provides solutions to how we can deliver public services within an ever-tightening fiscal environment. The LGA’s 
defaultRewiring Public Services
default is an ambitious programme which would allow local authorities, through greater local autonomy, to 
defaulthelp communit
defaulties to meet people’s future needs and aspirations and 
defaulthelp generate economic growth. 
default2.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultDemocratically elected councillors must be at the heart of any programme of public service reform. Councillors are 
defaultcrucial
default in
default reinvigorating local governance, ensuring strong democratic accountability, and 
defaultleading
default local government to make a difference, deliver and be trusted.
default&#xa0;
default2.3.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCentral government can learn much from how councils have delivered efficiencies and come together to share services, not just with other councils but with organisations in all areas of public services. However, councils could achieve much more if they were
default freed from unnecessary bureaucracy and the direction of artificial Whitehall silos. 
default&#xa0;
default&#xa0;
default3.1.
defaultPeople increasingly feel that English democracy is facing a crisis. Disillusionment with politics, frustration over unequal distribution of power in the United Kingdom,
default and low levels
default of trust in central government
default have led us to a place where the current model of public services is unsustainable. However well-intentioned Government reforms might be, it is 
defaultultimately 
defaultlocal leadership that 
defaultcan best deliver economic growth, transformed 
defaultpublic services and a rejuvenated democracy. 
default&#xa0;default3.2.
defaultIn 
defaultRewiring Public Services
default, the
default LGA
default has set out an approach to public service transformation that will give local people a clear say in the important matters that face them and their communities, and a local vote that matters once more. 
defaultThe
default challenges England faces require a different appro
defaultach that reflects the needs of local communities, based on joined-up services, economic 
defaultgrowth 
defaultand a new democratic deal. 
default&#xa0;default&#xa0;
default4.1.
defaultCommunity budgets 
defaultlook at the whole system rather than 
defaultindividual
default 
defaultservices; they are rooted in evidence; and they demand new models of investmen
defaultt to set up and sustain the most effective interventions.
default Independent analysis
default for the LGA of the work of the four community budget pilot areas showed that
default,
default if their proposals on health and social care, troubled families and work and skills were implemented across the country
default,
default up to £20 billion could be saved over five years. The four areas expect to see a range of wider benefits. For example Essex is redesig
defaultning its vocational skills such that it will create 
default8,000 additiona
defaultl apprenticeships by 2020, with 
defaulttraining better aligned to current and future vacancies in the area.
default 
default&#xa0;
default4.2.
defaultWhat is clear is the community budget led public service reform agenda offers a much g
defaultreater potential for ensuring better value for money and improved services. It is therefore essential that all Whitehall Departments buy into this approach and make positive moves 
defaultto devolve budgets and responsibility to the local level to enable local pub
defaultlic service providers to bring resources together to deliver more efficient public services with improved outcomes
default.
default&#xa0;
default4.3.
defaultThese findings are supported by an extensive body of evidence from councils, for example through the customer-led transformation programme
default and innovative procurement by councils following the introduction of the Public Services (Social Value) Act 2012.
