default5.1.
defaultPublic services in England face 
defaultchallenges which require a 
defaultfundamental
default response at both national and local level. 
defaultS
defaultervices must be transformed through local leadership by rebuilding democratic participation, rewiring public services, and revitalising the economy. The risks of staying the
default same far outweigh those of leading a transformation that ensures public services are effective, efficient and locally responsive.
default&#xa0;
default5.2.
defaultThe role of elected councillors is 
defaultcrucial 
defaultin ensuring communities can access responsive, effective, and accountable 
defaultservices. Local government could do much more to rewire public services and rebuild democratic participation. A fundamental redesign of the national framework of local democracy would ensure decisions about local arrangements are made by people who are acc
defaultountable to local voters. Reinvigorating this democratic relationship will give communities a meaningful say in the delivery of their services, no matter what form those services take.
