defaultthe Work Programme should help councils and their partners better support those who are hardest to reach. Despite good intentions, the model was designed, commissioned, implemented and delivered in isolation and at speed, preventing councils and local part
defaultners from offering expertise on client groups. In most cases, it has had the effect of providers operating in isolation from one another and local partners. Critically, the model has not led to successful outcomes for those 
defaultit is meant to help. March 2013 
defaultfigures suggest all Work Programme providers have failed to support Employment Support Allowance (ESA) claimants, averaging 5.3% aga
defaultinst contracted levels of 16.5%
default.
default June 2013 figures have not improved.
